e is credited with having found the True Cross in Jerusalem. She was born in about  248 , probably in Bithynia. However, in medieval England it was believed that she had been born in Britain, which greatly increased the popularity of the name there."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Helen Vicars was born in 1228, in Epperstone, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William Sampson about 1249, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1228–":"1228–Surnud","1224–1282":"1224–1282","1249–Female":"1249–Surnud","1228–Female":"1228–Surnud","1228":"1228","1249":"1249","1224":"1224","about 1249":"umbes 1249","1282":"1282","England":"England","Epperstone, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Epperstone, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Newark, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Newark, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Basford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Basford, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1228–":"1228–Kuollut","1224–1282":"1224–1282","1249–Female":"1249–Kuollut","1228–Female":"1228–Kuollut","1228":"1228","1249":"1249","1224":"1224","about 1249":"noin 1249","1282":"1282","England":"England","Epperstone, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Epperstone, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Newark, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Newark, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Basford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Basford, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1228–":"1228–Décédée","1224–1282":"1224–1282","1249–Female":"1249–Décédée","1228–Female":"1228–Décédée","1228":"1228","1249":"1249","1224":"1224","about 1249":"environ 1249","1282":"1282","England":"Angleterre","Epperstone, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Epperstone, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Newark, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Newark, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bas